div1.ab: The return of LV Wyckoff to the writ of Habeas Corpus hereto annexed
div1.p: In obedience to the writ of Habeas Corpus hereby annexed I do hereby certify and return to the Honorable John P Hoyt Judge of the Second Judicial District in the Territory of Washington; that before the coming to me of said writ; on the first day of November, A.D. 1881, at Seattle in the county of King in the Territory of Washington, the said Henry Imhof mentioned in said writ was placed in my custody as Deputy United States Marshall for the Territory aforesaid, by virtue of two committments issued by James P Ludlow, United States Commissioner for the said Judicial District in said Territory, copries of which are hereto annexed and that said Henry Imhof is now in my custody under said committments; all of which I certify, and I have his body before the said Judge, as by the said writ - I am commanded.
